-- Saudi Airlines Cargo Raises Handling 26% in First Half This Year
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-08-01T16:03:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/saudi-airlines-cargo-raises-handling-26-in-first-half-this-year.html
Saudi Airlines Cargo Co. increased
the cargo it carried by 26 percent in the first half of this
year to 251,500 tons from a year earlier on more exports to
 Europe ,  East Africa  and the United Arab Emirates.  “We experienced all-time records in May and June 2012,”
Fahad Hammad, Chief Executive Officer of Saudia Cargo, said in a
 statement on its website  dated July 29. “We expect the growth
to continue in the second half of 2012.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  